(Using the equality comparison operator on null)

Nada is nothing

Say "null doesn't equal mysterious"
Mystery is mysterious
say Mystery is Nada
say Mystery is nothing
say nothing is Mystery
say nothing is mysterious

Say "null equals itself"
say Nada is Nada
say Nada is nothing
say nobody is Nada
say nowhere is empty

Say "null can equal booleans"
Rightness is right
Wrongness is wrong
say Nada is Rightness
say Nada is Wrongness
say true is nothing
say false is nothing

Say "null equals zero, but not other numbers"
Int is 42
NegativeInt is -42
Float is 12.34
NegativeFloat is -12.34
ZeroInt is 0
ZeroFloat is 0.0
say Nada is Int
say Nada is NegativeInt
say Nada is Float
say Nada is NegativeFloat
say Nada is ZeroInt
say Nada is ZeroFloat
say 42 is nothing
say 12.34 is nothing
say 0 is nothing
say 0.0 is nothing
say -0 is nothing
say -0.0 is nothing

Say "null doesn't equal strings"
Str is "foo"
NullStr is "null"
EmptyStr is ""
say Nada is Str
say Nada is NullStr
say Nada is EmptyStr
say "foo" is null
say "null" is null
say "0" is null
